<div id="review_2849888188" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2849888188" />
    <a title="Seonaid" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12201799-seonaid"><img alt="Seonaid" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1345883765p2/12201799.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2849888188?book_show_action=true">Jun 24, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Seonaid" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Seonaid" href="/user/show/12201799-seonaid">Seonaid</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2849888188" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10640097767285737610">I wasn&apos;t sure about the book when I started reading it. The Mouse and his child, stuck together eternally, made me feel claustrophobic, and I could not accept that this was a children&apos;s book. Then, suddenly, it just clicked with me, and I started to love it, to the extent I could hardly then put it down.<br/><br/>To me, this is not a kid&apos;s book, though I have friends whose kids also love it; this is a book about identity, about growing up and becoming autonomous; this is a book about brutality, perseveran</span>
  <span id="freeText10640097767285737610" style="display:none">I wasn't sure about the book when I started reading it. The Mouse and his child, stuck together eternally, made me feel claustrophobic, and I could not accept that this was a children's book. Then, suddenly, it just clicked with me, and I started to love it, to the extent I could hardly then put it down.<br /><br />To me, this is not a kid's book, though I have friends whose kids also love it; this is a book about identity, about growing up and becoming autonomous; this is a book about brutality, perseverance, failure and ultimate success. I didn't find it an easy read, but I did find it beautiful, lyrical in places, and one of the most existentialist books I have ever read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10640097767285737610" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


